* Overall awards wrapper for RaceRoster upload.
*
* Purpose:          Runs OVERALL-RR.RSM to list top finishers and append them
*                   to the Race Roster upload file, then EXCLUDE.RSM so those
*                   runners do not appear again in age-group sections.
*
*                   EXCLUDE.RSM is print/processing only — it has no Destination
*                   and does not affect the upload file.
*
* IMPORTANT:        RaceRosterHeader.rsm MUST have run before this wrapper.
*                   It registers the upload gate (External Report To + ##NNN##).
*                   Without it, OVERALL-RR.RSM writes to disk but never uploads.
*
* Param 1 (%1):     Number of overall winners (e.g., 3).
* Param 2 (%2):     Sex label (FEMALE or MALE).
* Param 3 (%3):     Sex code (F or M).
* Param 4 (%4):     Destination filename (must start with ~, e.g. ~awards-5k.txt).
*                   Must match the filename passed to RaceRosterHeader.rsm.
*
* Example:          @OVERALL-RR.RSM 3 FEMALE F "~awards-5k.txt"
*
* See also:         Working example: C:\RunScore\SampleRaces\5k
*
OVERALL-RR.RSM %1 %2 %3 %4
EXCLUDE.RSM %1 %2 %3
